	<!-- When to Call for Furnace Service -->
	<section class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-white">
		<div class="container mx-auto px-4">
			<div class="text-center mb-12">
				<div class="flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
					<div class="w-10 h-1 bg-accent mr-4"></div>
					<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-primary font-heading">WHEN TO CALL FOR FURNACE SERVICE</h2>
					<div class="w-10 h-1 bg-accent ml-4"></div>
				</div>
				<p class="text-lg text-darkgray max-w-3xl mx-auto">
					Recognizing the signs that your furnace needs professional attention can help prevent major breakdowns and
					ensure your home stays warm and comfortable.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
				<!-- Unusual Noises -->
				<div class="bg-lightgray p-6 rounded-lg">
					<div class="flex items-center mb-4">
						<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-6 w-6 text-accent mr-3 flex-shrink-0" fill="none"
						     viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
							<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"
							      d="M15.536 8.464a5 5 0 010 7.072m2.828-9.9a9 9 0 010 12.728M5.586 15.536a5 5 0 01-.707-7.07m-2.122 9.9a9 9 0 010-12.728"/>
						</svg>
						<h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary">Unusual Noises</h3>
					</div>
					<p class="text-darkgray">
						Banging, rattling, whistling, or grinding sounds from your furnace are not normal and typically indicate a
						mechanical issue that requires professional attention.
					</p>
				</div>

				<!-- Insufficient Heat -->
				<div class="bg-lightgray p-6 rounded-lg">
					<div class="flex items-center mb-4">
						<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-6 w-6 text-accent mr-3 flex-shrink-0" fill="none"
						     viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
							<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"
							      d="M12 3v1m0 16v1m9-9h-1M4 12H3m15.364 6.364l-.707-.707M6.343 6.343l-.707-.707m12.728 0l-.707.707M6.343 17.657l-.707.707M16 12a4 4 0 11-8 0 4 4 0 018 0z"/>
						</svg>
						<h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary">Insufficient Heat</h3>
					</div>
					<p class="text-darkgray">
						If your furnace is running but not producing enough heat, or if some rooms are much colder than others, it's
						time to call for professional service.
					</p>
				</div>

				<!-- Rising Energy Bills -->
				<div class="bg-lightgray p-6 rounded-lg">
					<div class="flex items-center mb-4">
						<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-6 w-6 text-accent mr-3 flex-shrink-0" fill="none"
						     viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
							<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"
							      d="M17 9V7a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v6a2 2 0 002 2h2m2 4h10a2 2 0 002-2v-6a2 2 0 00-2-2H9a2 2 0 00-2 2v6a2 2 0 002 2zm7-5a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0z"/>
						</svg>
						<h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary">Rising Energy Bills</h3>
					</div>
					<p class="text-darkgray">
						An unexpected increase in your heating bills without a corresponding increase in usage often indicates that
						your furnace is operating inefficiently and needs service.
					</p>
				</div>

				<!-- Frequent Cycling -->
				<div class="bg-lightgray p-6 rounded-lg">
					<div class="flex items-center mb-4">
						<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-6 w-6 text-accent mr-3 flex-shrink-0" fill="none"
						     viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
							<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"
							      d="M4 4v5h.582m15.356 2A8.001 8.001 0 004.582 9m0 0H9m11 11v-5h-.581m0 0a8.003 8.003 0 01-15.357-2m15.357 2H15"/>
						</svg>
						<h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary">Frequent Cycling</h3>
					</div>
					<p class="text-darkgray">
						If your furnace turns on and off frequently, it may be short cycling due to overheating, thermostat issues,
						or other problems that require professional diagnosis.
					</p>
				</div>

				<!-- Yellow Pilot Light -->
				<div class="bg-lightgray p-6 rounded-lg">
					<div class="flex items-center mb-4">
						<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-6 w-6 text-accent mr-3 flex-shrink-0" fill="none"
						     viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
							<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z"/>
						</svg>
						<h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary">Yellow Pilot Light</h3>
					</div>
					<p class="text-darkgray">
						A healthy pilot light should be blue. If yours is yellow or flickering, it could indicate a ventilation
						problem or carbon monoxide leak, which requires immediate professional attention.
					</p>
				</div>

				<!-- Age of System -->
				<div class="bg-lightgray p-6 rounded-lg">
					<div class="flex items-center mb-4">
						<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-6 w-6 text-accent mr-3 flex-shrink-0" fill="none"
						     viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
							<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"
							      d="M8 7V3m8 4V3m-9 8h10M5 21h14a2 2 0 002-2V7a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v12a2 2 0 002 2z"/>
						</svg>
						<h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary">Age of System</h3>
					</div>
					<p class="text-darkgray">
						If your furnace is more than 15 years old, it may require more frequent service to maintain efficiency and
						reliability. Regular maintenance becomes even more important as systems age.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
